Aetna’s Consumer Health Services Clinical Analytics team creates innovative analytic tools to drive better decision making within the organization. We are currently seeking a Lead Data Scientist to join us in developing analytic tools and products to improve health outcomes in our Wellesley, MA or Hartford, CT location. This position will lead initiatives to develop predictive analytics and apply analytically derived insights to improve consumer engagement, enhance health outcomes and lower healthcare costs. Position Summary: The position will work with stakeholders across the organization to execute complex analytical projects. This role requires partnering with customers to solve important health care challenges using advanced statistical methods on an industry leading scalable technology platform. The Lead Data Scientist will work in a highly collaborative environment, often coordinating the work of other analysts, to develop analytical solutions that leverage data from diverse sources and deploying those solutions with agility and flexibility.   Fundamental Components: · Manages large and complex analytical projects from data exploration, to model building, performance evaluation and testing. · Uses strong knowledge of statistical algorithms and predictive models to investigate problems, detect patterns and recommend solutions.· Provides project guidance, technical advice, and mentorship to junior team members. · Uses strong programming skills to extract, explore and interpret large volumes of data in various forms.· Collaborates with business partners to understand their problems and goals, develop models, statistical analysis, data reports and performance metrics.   Background/Experience:· 7+  years related experience with healthcare data analytics, statistical analysis, predictive modeling, machine learning techniques, and visualization tools. · Solid understanding of healthcare industry, products, and systems and business strategies.· Strong knowledge of advanced analytics tools and languages to analyze large data sets from multiple data sources.· Experience in SAS or SQL programming languages.· Experience with big data technologies such as Python, R, Hive, Hadoop, and Tableau preferred.· Demonstrated ability to effectively communicate and negotiate across the business and in the external healthcare environment.· Demonstrated ability to communicate technical ideas and results to non-technical clients in written and verbal form.· Strong organizational, management and leadership skills.· Excellent analytical and problem solving skills 
